mpted=yes }}, ''The Public Interest'', Vol. 35, pp.&nbsp;103\u2013120.\n* [[Murray Rothbard|Rothbard, Murray N.]] (1995). [http://www.lewrockwell.com/2014/09/murray-n-rothbard/why-the-power-elite-loves-equality/ \"Egalitarianism and the Elites,\"] ''The Review of Austrian Economics'', Vol. 8, No. 2, pp.&nbsp;39\u201357.\n* [[Louis Rougier|Rougier, Louis]] (1974). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1974q1-00029 \"Philosophical Origins of the Idea of Natural Equality,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XVIII, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;29\u201338.\n* [[James Fitzjames Stephen|Stephen, James Fitzjames]] (1873). [https://archive.org/stream/libertyequality00stepgoog#page/n196/mode/2up \"Equality.\"] In: ''Liberty, Equality, Fraternity.'' New York: Holt & Williams, pp.&nbsp;189\u2013255.\n* [[Leslie Stephen|Stephen, Leslie]] (1891). [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2375306 \"Social Equality,\"] ''International Journal of Ethics,'' Vol. 1, No. 3, pp.&nbsp;261\u2013288.\n* Tonsor, Stephen J. (1979). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1979q1-00002 \"Liberty and Equality as Absolutes,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XXIII, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;2\u20139.\n* Tonsor, Stephen J. (1980). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1980q2-00134 \"Equality and Ancient Society,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XXIV, No. 2, pp.&nbsp;134\u2013141.\n* Tonsor, Stephen J. (1980). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1980q3-00238 \"The New Natural Law and the Problem of Equality,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XXIV, No. 3, pp.&nbsp;238\u2013247.\n* Tonsor, Stephen J. (1980). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1980q4-00345 \"Equality in the New Testament,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XXIV, No. 4, pp.&nbsp;345\u2013354.\n* Tonsor, Stephen J. (1981). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1981q1-00046 \"Equality: The Greek Historical Experience,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XXV, No. 1, pp.&nbsp;46\u201355.\n* Velasco, Gustavo R. (1974). [http://www.unz.org/Pub/ModernAge-1974q1-00021 \"On Equality and Egalitarianism,\"] ''The Modern Age'', Vol. XVIII, N